e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776205006744,"sessionId":"a2d33d5c-359f-4017-a94d-47c95c8de7b2","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":24217,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776204425822,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/a2d33d5c-359f-4017-a94d-47c95c8de7b2.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the sessions list. I need to identify active master-orchestrator sessions, excluding this cron session (e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e).\n\nSessions found:\n1. `cron:e7885813` — **THIS IS THE CURRENT SESSION** (excluded) — running, started 22:10 UTC\n2. `cron:6f3323ef` — running, started 1776199558073 (22:05 UTC), so ~11 minutes running — \"5p Progress Report - DTLX\"\n\n\n3. `telegram:direct:6053576134` — done, ended ~22:02 UTC — Lead's direct session (done, not active)\n4. `cron:ed2d0b5d` — running, started 1776195346099 (21:29 UTC) — \"5p Progress Report\" (QLHV), running ~1h 47m\n5. `main` — done (heartbeat poll), ended 22:11 UTC — not active\n6. `telegram:group:-5163901258` — still showing in the list but I need to check its actual status since it appeared earlier as ended\n\nLooking at the end timestamp 1776163783190 (21:49 UTC), it does have an endedAt value, but the status field says \"running\" — this is probably just a staleness issue. The real active sessions I should focus on are the cron jobs: e7885813 is excluded, so I'm looking at ed2d0b5d (running ~1h 47m) and 6f3323ef (running ~11m), plus maybe that telegram group session if it's still actually active. I need to verify which of these are genuinely still running versus which ones have ended. I'm seeing that telegram:group:-5163901258 has both an endedAt timestamp and a status of done, which suggests it's not actually active despite what the API returned. Looking at the active sessions, I have cron:ed2d0b5d and cron:6f3323ef still running, but I'm excluding the cron:e7885813 session since that's the current one. Let me calculate the duration for cron:ed2d0b5d by working backward from the current time of 22:16 UTC on April 14th.\n\nFor the other sessions, cron:6f3323ef started at 22:05 UTC and has been running for about 11 minutes. The telegram:direct:6053576134 session is marked as done, so I'll exclude it from the active count. I need to decide whether to include the telegram:group:-5163901258 session in my report—it has an endedAt timestamp suggesting it ended around 21:49 UTC, but the API is still reporting it as running, which is contradictory.\n\nLooking at the session data, it does have an endedAt value, so it appears to have terminated already. However, I'm seeing conflicting information across sessions—some show \"running\" status even though they have endedAt timestamps. I'll stick with what the API explicitly reports as \"running\" for my active sessions list.\n\nSo I've got two cron jobs that are genuinely active: cron:ed2d0b5d running the QLHV 5p progress report for about 47 minutes, and cron:6f3323ef running the DTLX 5p progress report for roughly 11 minutes. The telegram sessions are marked as done or appear to be done, so I'll exclude them from the report.\n\nNow I'm formatting this for the Lead and sending it via Telegram."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bhpncuseja0w_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 22:16 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 2\n• cron:ed2d0b5d: running — 5p Progress Report (QLHV) — ~1h 47m\n• cron:6f3323ef: running — 5p Progress Report (DTLX) — ~11m\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Blockers: none\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":9069,"output":914,"totalToken